Captain Lionel Messi has told FC Barcelona he wishes to leave the club immediately, a source confirmed on Tuesday. The club source said Messi, who has spent his entire career at FC Barcelona, informed the club about his desire to leave by sending a burofax, a service used in Spain to urgently dispatch a document that requires proof to third parties. The 33-year-old Argentine, who joined the club in 2000 as a youth player, has a contract with the Catalans until 2021. (Reuters/NAN) 